&lt;div class="post-text" itemprop="text"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Use the &lt;code&gt;final&lt;/code&gt; keyword  (like in Java etc):&lt;/p&gt;



&lt;pre class="lang-php prettyprint-override"&gt;&lt;code&gt;class fooBase{

  final public function something(){

  }
}

class foo extends fooBase{

  public function __construct(){
    echo $this-&amp;gt;something(); // &amp;lt;- should be the parent class method
  }

  public function something(){ 
    // this method should not be allowed to be created
  }
}
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;See &lt;a href="http://php.net/manual/en/language.oop5.final.php" rel="nofollow"&gt;PHP Final keyword&lt;/a&gt;. Note that &lt;code&gt;foo&lt;/code&gt; will still have a method &lt;code&gt;something&lt;/code&gt;, but &lt;code&gt;something&lt;/code&gt; will only come from &lt;code&gt;fooBase&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code&gt;foo&lt;/code&gt; can't override it.&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;

